# Myah OSS — environment configuration template.
#
# ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │  DO NOT EDIT THIS FILE BY HAND ON A FRESH INSTALL.              │
# │                                                                 │
# │  Run this once instead:                                         │
# │                                                                 │
# │      ./scripts/setup-myah-oss.sh                                │
# │                                                                 │
# │  It generates secure random values for every required secret,   │
# │  writes them to BOTH this file and ~/.hermes/.env so the        │
# │  platform and Hermes agent agree, and patches your Hermes       │
# │  config.yaml to enable the Myah platform adapter.               │
# │                                                                 │
# │  Re-run with --rotate to regenerate every secret.               │
# └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# Quickstart:
#
#   1. Install Hermes on the host:
#        curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/main/scripts/install.sh | bash
#
#   2. Install the Myah plugin:
#        hermes plugins install T3-Venture-Labs-Limited/myah-hermes-plugin
#        (press Enter to skip the MYAH_ADAPTER_AUTH_KEY prompt — the
#         setup script in step 3 fills it in)
#
#   3. From this directory, run the bootstrap script:
#        ./scripts/setup-myah-oss.sh
#
#   4. Add an LLM provider key to ~/.hermes/.env, e.g.:
#        echo 'OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...' >> ~/.hermes/.env
#
#   5. Start Hermes:
#        hermes gateway run                  # foreground
#        hermes gateway install && hermes gateway start  # OR: systemd
#
#   6. Start the platform:
#        docker compose up -d
#
#   7. Open http://localhost:8080
#
# If a step fails, see docs/troubleshooting.md or re-run
# scripts/setup-myah-oss.sh with --rotate.

# ─── REQUIRED — generated by setup-myah-oss.sh ────────────────────────
#
# Shared bearer token between this platform and your host Hermes.
# Identical value goes in:
#   - this file (MYAH_AGENT_BEARER_TOKEN)
#   - ~/.hermes/.env three times:
#       MYAH_AGENT_BEARER_TOKEN=<same>
#       MYAH_ADAPTER_AUTH_KEY=<same>      (what the plugin actually reads)
#       API_SERVER_KEY=<same>             (Hermes upstream api_server)
#
# All four MUST match or chat requests get 401. The setup script keeps
# them in sync.
MYAH_AGENT_BEARER_TOKEN=

# Fernet key for the oauth_session table (used when a user connects an
# OAuth provider via Composio / Hermes auth flow). The platform falls
# back to a built-in (insecure) default if unset — setup-myah-oss.sh
# always writes a real value here.
OAUTH_SESSION_TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# HMAC secret for the platform's own session cookies / JWT signing.
# An empty key falls back to a generated value persisted to a sidecar
# file (.myah_secret_key), which works but is non-portable across
# containers. setup-myah-oss.sh writes a real value here.
MYAH_SECRET_KEY=

# ─── OPTIONAL — Hermes gateway location (defaults usually work) ───────
#
# The platform reaches your host-side ``hermes gateway start`` process
# via host.docker.internal. Defaults match upstream's hermes layout —
# only override if you customized hermes ports.
#
# MYAH_HERMES_CHAT_PORT=8642    # Hermes core api_server (/v1/runs, /health)
# MYAH_GATEWAY_PORT=8643        # Myah plugin standalone runner (/myah/*)
# MYAH_HERMES_WEB_PORT=9119     # `hermes dashboard` web UI
#
# (The deprecated alias MYAH_HERMES_GATEWAY_PORT is still honored but
# triggers a one-line deprecation warning at boot. Use MYAH_GATEWAY_PORT
# instead — it matches the plugin's own env var name.)
#
# If you ran hermes on a different host (not localhost), override:
# MYAH_AGENT_HOST=192.168.1.50

# ─── OPTIONAL — observability ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Sentry DSN for the platform backend (Python). The frontend Sentry DSN
# is baked at build time via PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN — see Dockerfile.
# Leave unset for self-hosted deployments without an external Sentry
# project — Myah does NOT send telemetry by default.
# SENTRY_DSN=

# ─── ADVANCED — override the platform image ────────────────────────────
#
# By default docker-compose tags the platform image as
# ``myah/platform:latest`` (a local-only tag) and BUILDS it from
# Dockerfile on first ``docker compose up``. A fresh clone works
# without any registry auth.
#
# To skip the local build and pull a pre-published image instead:
#   MYAH_PLATFORM_IMAGE=ghcr.io/your-org/myah-platform:v0.1.0
#
# To run a custom local build:
#   docker build -t myah/platform:local .
#   MYAH_PLATFORM_IMAGE=myah/platform:local

# ─── REFERENCE ONLY — written to ~/.hermes/.env by setup script ───────
#
# These are NOT read by the platform — they live in ~/.hermes/.env and
# are listed here so you can see what setup-myah-oss.sh writes on the
# Hermes side:
#
# MYAH_AGENT_BEARER_TOKEN=<same as above>
# MYAH_ADAPTER_AUTH_KEY=<same as above>
# API_SERVER_KEY=<same as above>
# API_SERVER_ENABLED=true
# MYAH_PLATFORM_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8080
# MYAH_USER_ID=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
# MYAH_ALLOW_ALL_USERS=true
# MYAH_HOME_CHAT=disabled
# MYAH_HOME_CHANNEL=disabled
#
# And in ~/.hermes/config.yaml:
#
# gateway:
#   platforms:
#     myah:
#       enabled: true
